    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Fuel System - Assembly - Secondary Fuel
        Filter Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Secondary Fuel Filter Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f3001310" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figN11/N11020.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Secondary fuel filter assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter cap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter element</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel return tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Screw, 8/32 x 3/8 in (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Viton O-ring, size #112</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Secondary fuel filter housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M16 fuel return fitting</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 left and right cylinder head fuel tube assembly fitting (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Fuel Pressure (EFP) switch</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The engine will not run without the secondary fuel filter element. When installed properly the
                    secondary fuel filter element pushes down the fuel return tube which opens a valve, allowing fuel to
                    flow into the filter housing.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring gasket into the base of the fuel filter housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install return tube assembly over O-ring and secure with two 8/32 x 3/8 in. screws. Tighten
                screws to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_208.xml" xrefid="E30013B" appearance="hottext">special torque
                    <xref refid="E30013B"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install fuel filter element over return tube. Rotate element slightly until filter engages
                teeth and can be moved up and down against spring pressure.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a coating of clean diesel fuel to a new O-ring and install onto fuel filter cap.
                Thread fuel filter cap onto filter housing and tighten to special torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new O-rings onto M12 and M16 fittings and install in fuel filter housing. Tighten
                fittings to special torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
